-- Texas Attorney General to Investigate Emissions Violation at BP Refinery
-- Katarzyna Klimasinska
-- 2010-07-29T18:32:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/texas-attorney-general-to-investigate-emissions-violation-at-bp-refinery.html

          
          
             Texas Attorney General  Greg Abbott 
will investigate air contaminants released at the Texas City
refinery owned by London-based  BP Plc .  
 A violation involving the release of 500,000 pounds of
pollutants from April 6 to May 16 was referred by the  Texas
Commission on Environmental Quality  on July 23, spokesman Thomas
Kelley said.  
 “We’re obliged to look at the whole matter under our
jurisdiction at this point as the attorney general, and we
certainly will do that,” he said by phone from Austin today.  
 The plant has processing capacity of 455,790 barrels a day,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  
